@startuml technology-sequence-observability-query-path-v1
title Observability Query Path (Operational Scenario)

participant "DashboardServer\nAPP-020" as APP_020
database "EventStore\nAPP-001" as APP_001

APP_020 -> APP_001: query_open_clarification_requests(phase_visit_interval, clarification_state_filter)
APP_001 --> APP_020: clarification_request_status_list(open_or_pending_answer)
APP_020 -> APP_001: query_pending_sprint_review_scope(sprint_id, review_decision_state_filter)
APP_001 --> APP_020: sprint_review_queue(pending_or_needs_revision_decision)
APP_020 -> APP_001: query_phase_gate_timeline(phase_transition_interval)
APP_001 --> APP_020: phase_gate_timeline_entries()
APP_020 -> APP_001: query_latest_checkpoint_state()
APP_001 --> APP_020: latest_checkpoint_state(snapshot_ref, updated_at)
APP_020 -> APP_020: assemble_review_and_control_monitoring_view()

note right of APP_020
Scenario scope: read-side observability only (no writes).
Dashboard observability features covered:
- open clarification requests and answer status
- pending sprint-review scope and decision state
- phase/gate lifecycle timeline and latest checkpoint
Design rule: prefer explicit read-model queries over opaque bundle names.
If one transport endpoint is required for UI efficiency, model it as
an orchestrating facade that composes these domain queries.
Business relevance:
- supports BPR-003 clarification lifecycle monitoring
- supports BIA-001 sprint-review interaction monitoring
No replay/bootstrap or decision-control sequence is implied.
end note
@enduml
